Comedian Njugush says fans should expect a lot of laughter on his new show on NTV. Speaking to Word Is, Njugush said it's is a comedy show. "As always, they should expect nothing serious but laughter. It is what people have been asking, so they won't be disappointed," he said. Fan received the news of the show positively after its announcement on social media. Njugush says the show also features his wife Celestine Ndinda. "It is a situational comedy with my wife and other acts, a sketch of what we have been doing online. It feels good to have created this," he said. The show will premiere on 25th. Details of time will be given on a later date.